parameters: There you are! It's good to see you up and about. By the way,
It was my fathers. He passed it down to me. I thought I'd lost it.
Things aren't looking so good. \C[4]Winter\C[0]'s gone, \C[4]Davos\C[0] abandoned
We worry about tomorrow when it gets here. Right now the sun is
warm, the breeze is cool, and the company is good.
Let's just enjoy this, even if it's only a moment in time.
Well, with \C[4]Davos\C[0] in parts unknown and \C[4]Winter\C[0]
following him, the best we can hope for is that they're successful
In the meantime, if what \C[2]Yellow Jacket\C[0] said was true,
\C[6]Ishtar\C[0] is being manipulated by \C[6]The Order of the Wind\C[0]
Until new information surfaces on the \C[6]Final Seal\C[0], maybe
we should head for \C[6]Ishtar\C[0], root out the evil influences
in the government and bring this war to an end.
We'll never repel \C[2]Bahamut\C[0] if the whole world is busy
Maybe we'll even find a way to check in on \C[4]Davos\C[0] and
\C[4]Winter\C[0] as we go. And I bet \C[4]Rex\C[0] from the

I wonder if \C[4]Davos\C[0] might even run into that girl he
saved at the camp? Maybe she can help them as well. She looked
sorta like a healer, like me.
Alright, enough 4th wall breaking. Let's get back to the game!
Well look who's awake! When we saw you two cliff dive off the
coast, we figured you for dead. Looks like I lost a bet.
That's a bet I'm glad you lost. I can't begin to thank you
enough. Say... aren't you the boat captain that gave us a ride to \C[6]Crescant Island\C[0]?
That's right! Business has been booming for me ever since, too. I
even managed to hire a proper crew and got myself a right seaworthy
Before we set sail, I have something for you.
There's plenty o' docks around \C[3]Spyria\C[0]. If you ever
need us and we aren't around, just go to one and blow the whistle.
Press the "\C[6]Vessel Control\C[0]" button to launch the ship.
While out to sea, press this button to switch between walking
around on the ship and sailing the ship. Press the action button
to disembark when beside of land.
\C[4]\N[5]\C[0]? I think I saw him below deck.
I'm fine with taking you anywhere you need to go. Fate of
You pulled through after all! Looks like the captain owes me
a seafood dinner. ...not that there's much other types of dinners
You pulled through after all! Looks like the captain owes me
a seafood dinner. ...not that there's much other types of dinners
Glad to see you're up and about. If you're looking for your friend,
you'll find her on the bow.
The captain's still in charge around here, but he's amicable to
giving you a ride anywhere you need to go.
You must be \C[4]\N[5]\C[0]. A pleasure to meet ya! The name's \C[4]Rex\C[0].
A fair sailor, decent sword-arm and reformed pirate.
A pirate? How'd you end up on a merchant vessel?
It's a long story, but a great man saved me from certain death.
After that, I decided to turn my life around and, well... here I am!
I'll spread the legend of \C[4]Auryn, the Blade\C[0] far and wide!
He'd hate that. But you should do it anyways. The world needs
I still can't believe \C[4]Auryn\C[0] is dead. I'd never seen
anyone fight like him. If I ever see those \C[2]LEGION\C[0] punks
In moments of pain, we seek revenge. But unchecked, it consumes us.
The battles ahead require a scalpel, not a club.
I'm grateful for the chance to work on this merchant vessel,
but if I'm honest with myself, it's pretty boring.
I only heard legends. I didn't think it was real!
Best to keep our distance. Any closer an' she'd rip the ship apart!
